"Wu W.B., Woodroofe M., Mentz G.","Isotonic regression: Another look at the changepoint problem",2001,"Biometrika","88","3",,"793","804",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0043243941&partnerID=40&md5=9cf7a9838661f2526ce5ecee1211b379","Department of Statistics, University of Michigan, Ann Arbor, MI 48109, United States","Wu, W.B., Department of Statistics, University of Michigan, Ann Arbor, MI 48109, United States; Woodroofe, M., Department of Statistics, University of Michigan, Ann Arbor, MI 48109, United States; Mentz, G., Department of Statistics, University of Michigan, Ann Arbor, MI 48109, United States","A test based on isotonic regression is developed for monotonie trends in short range dependent sequences and is applied to Argentina rainfall data and global warming data. This test provides another perspective for changepoint problems. The isotonic test is shown to be more powerful than some existing tests for trend. © 2001 Biometrika Trust.","Changepoint problem; Isotonic regression; Penalised likelihood function; Short range dependence",,,,,,,"Bhattacharya, P.K., Some aspects of change-point analysis (1994) Change-Point Problems, pp. 28-56. , Ed. E. Carlstein, H. Müller and D. Siegmund, Hayward, CA: Inst. Math. Statist; Brillinger, D.R., Consistent detection of a monotonie trend superposed on a stationary time series (1989) Biometrika., 76, pp. 23-30; Brockwell, P.J., Davis, R.A., Time Series: Theory and Methods (1991) New York: Springer.; Brodsky, B.E., Darkhovsky, B.S., Nonparamctric Methods in Change Point Problems (1993) Dordrecht: Klmver.; Darkhovsky, B.S., Nonparametric methods in change-point problems: A general approach and some concrete algorithms (1994) Change-Point Problems, pp. 99-107. , Ed. E. Carlstein, H. Müller and D. Siegmund, Hayward, CA: Inst. Math. Statist; Delworth, T.L., Knutson, T.R., Simulation of early 20th century global warming (2000) Science, 287, pp. 2246-2250; Groeneboom, P., Pyke, R., Asymptotic normality of statistics based on the convex minorants of empirical distribution functions (1983) Ann. Prob., 11, pp. 328-345; Lavielle, M., Moulines, É., Détection de ruptures multiples dans la moyenne d'un processus aléatoire (1997) C. R. Acad. Sci. Paris Ser. I Math., 324, pp. 239-243; Lombard, F., Hart, J.D., The analysis of change-point data with dependent errors (1994) ChangePoint Problems, pp. 194-209. , Ed. E. Carlstein, H. Müller and D. Siegmund, Hayward, CA: Inst. Math. Statist; Maxwell, M., Woodroofe, M., Central limit theorems for additive functionals of Markov chains (2000) Ann. Prob., 28, pp. 713-724; Melillo, J.M., Climate change: Warm, warm on the Range (1999) Science, 283, pp. 183-184; Meyer, M., Woodroofe, M., On the decrees of freedom in shape-restricted regression Ann (2000) Statist., 28, pp. 1083-1104; Peligrad, M., Recent advances in the central limit theorem and its weak invariance principle for mixing sequences of random variables (a survey) (1986) Dependence in Probability and Statistics: a Survey of Recent Results, pp. 193-224. , Ed. E. Eberlein and M. Taqqu, Boston, MA: Birkhauser; Robertson, T., Wright, F.T., Dykstra, R.L., Order Restricted Statistical Inference (1988) New York: John Wiley.; Shaban, S.A., Change point problem and two-phase regression: An annotated bibliography (1980) Int. Statist. Rei, 48, pp. 83-93; Siegmund, D., Boundary crossing probabilities and statistical applications (1986) Ann. Statist., 14, pp. 361-404; Woodroofe, M., Sun, J., Testing uniformity versus a monotone density (1999) Ann. Statist., 27, pp. 338-360; Woodward, W.A., Gray, H.L., Global warming and the problem of testing for trend in timeseries data (1993) J. Climate, 6, pp. 953-962","Wu, W.B.; Department of Statistics, University of Michigan, Ann Arbor, MI 48109, United States; email: wbwu@umich.edu",,,,,,,,00063444,,BIOKA,,"English","Biometrika",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0043243941
